msgctxt "Talk01_01"
msgid ""
"<1.so>If you're interested, may I help you\n"
"change your horse's <2.se_co>gear<3.re_co> or "
"<4.se_co>mane<5.re_co>?<6.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: set_colour (blue)
#. 5: reset_colour
#. 6: choice
msgctxt "Talk01_02"
msgid ""
"<1.so>So you'd like me to change the <2.se_co>gear <3.re_co>or\n"
"<4.se_co>mane <5.re_co>on this little one again, correct?<6.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: sound
msgctxt "Talk01_1"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Oh? Your horse doesn't seem to\n"
"be tamed. At all.\n"
"\n"
"<2.so>Did you just catch it, by any chance?\n"
"Please spend some time showing this\n"
"sweetie you care, and then come back."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: sound
msgctxt "Talk01_2"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hm? This little one doesn't seem to trust\n"
"you just yet...\n"
"\n"
"<2.so>Spend some time showing this little love\n"
"how much you care, and you'll tame it in\n"
"no time."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "Talk01_3"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Nice! This little one has calm eyes,\n"
"but it doesn't fully trust you yet.\n"
"\n"
"You need to show it some more love!\n"
"Do that and I'll be happy to help you\n"
"out with some <2.se_co>gear<3.re_co>."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "Talk01_4"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Wow! This one's eyes are positively\n"
"sparkling with affection!\n"
"\n"
"I can tell this little one is just head over\n"
"heels for you. That settles it! I'll gladly\n"
"help you out with some <2.se_co>gear<3.re_co>!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Talk02"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Oh, but you should know I'm only\n"
"interested in horses that are raised\n"
"with lots of love!\n"
"How's your horse faring on that front?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "Talk04"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Aw, that's too bad... Please come back\n"
"again when you're ready to change your\n"
"horse's <2.se_co>gear<3.re_co>."
msgstr ""

